What should we do?
Should we go up

18:18.174 --> 18:19.266
or should we
just go back down?

18:19.375 --> 18:21.036
This is supposed to be
the best service, ever.

18:21.144 --> 18:22.168
I don't care.

18:22.278 --> 18:24.678
Did you hear about Oahu,
what happened there?

18:24.781 --> 18:25.770
Why? What happened?

18:25.882 --> 18:27.907
Well, my dad just
called from KCK.

18:28.017 --> 18:30.417
Reception's, like,
major shit out here.

18:30.520 --> 18:33.284
But he said something
about some murders.

18:35.491 --> 18:36.458
Wow.

18:36.826 --> 18:38.657
There's no service.

18:38.962 --> 18:40.293
Flat line.

18:40.396 --> 18:42.023
I'm in and out,
mostly out.

18:42.498 --> 18:44.056
Wait.
This is in Honolulu?

18:44.167 --> 18:45.930
Dad wants us to leave.

18:46.035 --> 18:48.230
I think he's in major
overreaction mode, okay?

18:48.338 --> 18:50.033
Some newlyweds were
killed somewhere, he said.

18:50.139 --> 18:51.163
That's what happened.

18:51.274 --> 18:52.366
Yeah.

18:52.475 --> 18:53.840
That's awful.

18:54.243 --> 18:57.337
I mean, we were just there,
like, the day before yesterday.

18:57.447 --> 18:59.438
We have been planning this for,
like, five-and-a-half months!

18:59.549 --> 19:01.881
Does he not even know
it's a different island?

19:01.985 --> 19:03.577
What did your dad say?

19:03.686 --> 19:06.712
I mean, do they know who did
it? Do they know anything?

19:06.823 --> 19:08.757
He says that they're
looking for two people.

19:08.858 --> 19:11.292
A man and a woman.
That's all I got.

19:11.394 --> 19:14.955
<i>It's like that movie, huh?
Natural Born Killers.</i>

19:16.165 --> 19:18.224
Oh, my God, that movie,
like, totally freaked me out.

19:18.334 --> 19:19.528
When his head was doing
that thing... Majorly.

19:22.505 --> 19:24.666
Well, what do you think?

19:24.774 --> 19:26.765
I mean,
it was Oahu, not here.

19:27.376 --> 19:30.174
Well, speak now or
forever hold your peace.

19:33.149 --> 19:35.913
Well, hey, I mean,
it's our honeymoon, right?

19:36.018 --> 19:37.178
Why don't you guys
come with us?

19:37.286 --> 19:39.754
We're going all the way to Kalalau
Beach, all the way to the end.

19:40.890 --> 19:43.882
Wait, you guys are,
like, newlyweds?

19:45.294 --> 19:46.454
Yeah.

19:51.067 --> 19:52.432
Have a swell honeymoon.

19:52.535 --> 19:53.627
Wait!

19:53.870 --> 19:56.498
Stop! Don't make me run.

19:57.974 --> 19:59.441
You guys are such cowards.

20:06.649 --> 20:12.451
Well, I exit here. Be safe.
Some hard yards ahead.

20:13.456 --> 20:17.222
Are you... Are you
camping over at Secret Falls?

20:19.595 --> 20:20.789
I read all about it
in the guidebook.

20:23.998 --> 20:25.192
Yeah, just for the day.

20:25.299 --> 20:28.097
I had to run back to the
truck for a little butane.

20:28.202 --> 20:30.500
Well, how close is it?

20:30.605 --> 20:32.436
Well, it's like
everything else in Hawaii.

20:32.540 --> 20:34.235
It's as close
as far away gets.

20:34.342 --> 20:35.366
Baby.
What?

20:35.476 --> 20:36.738
It sounds so romantic.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.812
Yeah, but I'd like to get
to the beach by sunset.

20:38.913 --> 20:41.609
But it's only like, what, like, a
mile or something? It's, like, nothing.

20:41.716 --> 20:45.049
Honey, come on. Maybe we
should give the man his privacy.

20:45.553 --> 20:48.613
Don't matter to me.
Plenty of Eden to go around.

20:58.866 --> 21:00.163
What?

21:00.268 --> 21:01.257
Nothing.

21:03.004 --> 21:04.938
One mile?

21:05.039 --> 21:06.438
One. Serious?

21:06.541 --> 21:08.099
Yeah.
Cool!

21:08.743 --> 21:10.176
Hey, wait up!

21:39.874 --> 21:41.000
Wow!

21:41.809 --> 21:47.270
Well, I do believe
she's clotheless.

21:47.381 --> 21:49.508
Hey, there.

21:49.617 --> 21:50.982
I do believe he is, too.

22:00.995 --> 22:02.428
This is Gina!

22:03.765 --> 22:05.824
Did he mention
Gina before?

22:06.467 --> 22:08.992
Crazy-ass love of
my crazy-ass life!

22:10.304 --> 22:11.703
He has now.

22:11.806 --> 22:16.038
Okay. So, they're,
like, a couple?

22:20.014 --> 22:21.948
Y'all coming in or what?

22:22.650 --> 22:25.084
Baby, are we
going in or not?

22:25.787 --> 22:29.382
Yeah, in a minute. Let me see
if I can get some reception.

22:30.758 --> 22:31.816
Okay.

22:46.874 --> 22:48.466
That's nice.

22:51.746 --> 22:56.410
I hope we're not intruding
on your private paradise here.

22:56.551 --> 23:00.647
Forget it, Nicko's always
bringing home strays.

23:02.323 --> 23:05.315
Mrs. Cydney Anderson.
We're newlyweds.

23:05.426 --> 23:08.190
Miss Gina Struggs.
We're not.

23:18.973 --> 23:20.372
You are so dead.

23:35.890 --> 23:36.948
Okay.

23:40.728 --> 23:43.128
Here we go. Come on.

23:50.238 --> 23:55.369
"Thursday on Oahu. Possibly
mainlanders on their honeymoon.

23:57.845 --> 24:00.143
"Teeth and
fingerprints removed.

24:00.781 --> 24:05.980
"Have reason to believe killers
may have jumped islands to Kauai. ' '

24:11.592 --> 24:12.718
Are you shitting me?

24:12.827 --> 24:15.295
No, these girls on
the trail told us.

24:16.497 --> 24:18.863
I feel like
maybe we saw someone.

24:19.033 --> 24:21.433
They know who it was
who did the killing?

24:21.535 --> 24:23.127
I don't think so.

24:32.980 --> 24:36.677
"Security cameras
released photo of suspect. ' '

24:47.128 --> 24:51.292
You know what I heard? A few
people die out here every year.

24:51.799 --> 24:55.667
They just stand under a waterfall,
get hit by some falling rock.

24:55.770 --> 25:00.002
Or maybe they just slip and
go right on over. Vanish.

25:02.376 --> 25:06.904
Who knows how? Or even why.
Could be the wages of sin.

25:10.785 --> 25:13.845
How you doing, Hot Wheels?

25:13.955 --> 25:15.183
I'm good.

25:18.526 --> 25:22.462
That's two lies in one day. It
comes naturally to you, don't it?

25:25.533 --> 25:27.592
Are you following us, Kale?

25:30.438 --> 25:33.339
You know, it ain't the fact
that you deceived us.

25:33.441 --> 25:35.966
Every man's got a pack
of lies in him, right?

25:36.444 --> 25:40.107
It's just that you thought we
was foolish enough to buy it.

25:42.149 --> 25:43.480
I'm sorry, I don't...

25:43.584 --> 25:45.108
What did you think,
anyway?

25:45.219 --> 25:46.686
Just 'cause we choose
to look a certain way

25:46.787 --> 25:49.813
that makes us,
what, desperados?

25:50.558 --> 25:52.219
No, I don't think...
Jesus, man.

25:52.326 --> 25:55.784
You know, sometimes it feels
like the whole world's just

25:55.896 --> 25:57.386
spitting in my face.

26:01.435 --> 26:02.732
Excuse me.

26:04.405 --> 26:08.865
Look. I thought you said you
were going to Lumahai Beach.

26:08.976 --> 26:12.104
"Going to that area. ' '
That's what we said.

26:12.213 --> 26:15.273
Well, you didn't say you
were doing the trail, so...

26:15.416 --> 26:17.247
Well, neither did you.

26:17.918 --> 26:22.480
Look. We offered you a ride. You
didn't want it. You didn't take it.

26:23.124 --> 26:26.719
So, I don't really understand
what the issue is between us.

26:27.561 --> 26:28.619
Kale?

26:34.201 --> 26:36.066
Joy and happiness here?

26:37.038 --> 26:38.903
No, I think we're good.

26:40.674 --> 26:42.039
Outstanding.

26:44.478 --> 26:46.002
How far you going,
Hot Wheels?

26:46.113 --> 26:49.549
Playing it by ear. You?

26:49.650 --> 26:50.912
Probably the next beach.

26:52.319 --> 26:53.286
What's it called?

26:53.387 --> 26:54.911
Hanakapi'ai.

26:55.022 --> 26:57.115
That one, yeah. Maybe
there, maybe further.

26:57.224 --> 26:59.419
Need permits to go further.

27:03.431 --> 27:05.797
Should have
given us a ride, man.

27:07.134 --> 27:08.328
Come on.

27:18.446 --> 27:23.440
So, after a $45 taxi ride, we
wind up at the Ocean View Hotel.

27:23.551 --> 27:25.212
Sounds nice, doesn't it?

27:25.319 --> 27:29.756
Problem is it hadn't actually
had an ocean view since 1987,

27:29.857 --> 27:32.485
when these high-rises
went up across the street.

27:33.160 --> 27:36.288
Jesus. Everyone's like,
"Waikiki is so great!"

27:36.397 --> 27:39.093
Honestly, it's getting
on my last nerve.

27:45.272 --> 27:46.364
Are we okay?

27:46.474 --> 27:47.941
Yeah. Let's keep an
eye on our time, okay?

27:48.042 --> 27:50.203
Yeah, but do those packs belong
to who I think they belong to?

27:50.311 --> 27:52.211
Yeah, they said they were
doing the trail all along.

27:52.313 --> 27:53.837
I don't know,
maybe they were.

27:53.948 --> 27:56.416
Shit, it's 1:30 already.
Come on, let's go.

27:59.787 --> 28:01.914
Hey, baby,
you want to break this down?

28:02.022 --> 28:03.785
We should be
clackalacking, too.

28:03.891 --> 28:04.949
Okey-dokey.

28:05.059 --> 28:06.083
Thank you.

28:08.362 --> 28:10.557
So, you guys don't
mind if we tag along?

28:10.664 --> 28:13.394
I mean, we're all
going to the same place.

28:13.868 --> 28:15.301
It's fine with me.

28:17.004 --> 28:18.835
Yeah. Are you kidding?

28:21.175 --> 28:22.574
Did you take the permits?

28:22.676 --> 28:23.802
No, I didn't touch them.

28:24.411 --> 28:27.073
Well, I put them right
here in this brochure.

28:28.015 --> 28:30.313
Did you leave
them at the store?

28:30.684 --> 28:34.984
No. I'm pretty sure I put...
No, I'm positive I put... Shit!

29:00.948 --> 29:02.745
While we're
still young, Cliff?

29:04.218 --> 29:05.685
Yeah, one sec!

29:13.627 --> 29:15.151
We leave no man behind.

29:15.329 --> 29:16.887
These are some hard yards.

29:34.381 --> 29:38.147
Guess you can't have rainbows
without a little rain. Right?

29:48.929 --> 29:52.194
You hear that Cliff here
is a big screenplay writer?

29:52.566 --> 29:54.761
You write for the movies?

29:55.302 --> 29:57.065
Whoopty-tah.

29:57.171 --> 29:58.160
Yeah, we say
screenwriter.

29:58.272 --> 30:00.365
He's on the prowl for
a new story. Sorry.

30:00.474 --> 30:01.771
You know, I could tell
you shit you ain't seen

30:01.875 --> 30:03.399
in no Hollywood movie before.

30:03.510 --> 30:05.102
You watch yourself now.

30:05.212 --> 30:06.201
What?

30:06.380 --> 30:08.348
What, what?
You know what.

30:08.449 --> 30:12.146
Maybe Cliff here can change
the names to protect the guilty.

30:12.319 --> 30:13.308
You guys do that
in movies, right?

30:13.420 --> 30:14.444
Yeah.

30:14.555 --> 30:16.580
You know Johnny Depp?
He knows Nic Cage.

30:16.724 --> 30:18.089
You see him playing me in some movie?

30:18.192 --> 30:19.659
Baby, you know Nic Cage?

30:19.760 --> 30:21.625
Yeah. Yeah, I do now.

30:22.029 --> 30:24.589
No. See, me, myself, I like
that Johnny Depp better.

30:24.698 --> 30:29.067
I mean, he is just dreamy. I
mean, the way he looks at you.

30:29.169 --> 30:32.627
Jesus Christ. Honey!
It all starts with story.

30:32.740 --> 30:33.729
Am I right, Cliff?

30:33.841 --> 30:34.865
Yeah.

30:35.409 --> 30:38.276
You know, I once made a surprise
visit in a certain dictator's palace

30:38.379 --> 30:39.607
on the Tigris River?

30:39.713 --> 30:42.614
Newly evacuated. Still
smell the Havana tobacco

30:42.716 --> 30:44.013
hanging in the air.

30:44.118 --> 30:46.416
We were tasked with finding
perishable intel, computer dish,

30:46.520 --> 30:47.578
shit like that.

30:47.688 --> 30:49.451
But in the master bathroom,

30:49.556 --> 30:52.116
about the size of fucking
Ethiopia, by the way,

30:52.226 --> 30:54.285
there's golden
dolphins for faucets.

30:54.395 --> 30:57.023
There was this lock box
bolted to the floor,

30:57.131 --> 30:59.190
had his initials
engraved on top.

30:59.300 --> 31:00.824
We started beating on
that fucking lock...

31:00.934 --> 31:02.902
Wait, Iraq?
You were in Iraq?

31:03.003 --> 31:04.061
Yeah, first in.

31:04.738 --> 31:06.296
Me and my wolf pack.

31:06.407 --> 31:09.808
Fuck those pictures you saw of
the 4th Infantry. That was later.

31:09.910 --> 31:12.037
What I'm giving you now
is God's real shit.

31:12.146 --> 31:14.614
He is not supposed to be
talking about this stuff.

31:14.715 --> 31:19.550
So, inside this box,
I figured maybe cash,

31:20.254 --> 31:22.620
<i>maybe a set of
pearl-handled pistolas.</i>

31:22.723 --> 31:26.819
Hell, maybe some damn fine
presidential-grade hashish.

31:26.927 --> 31:29.691
We finally burned it open
with a 50-grain det cord.

31:29.797 --> 31:31.697
It's a handy tool, det cord. Yeah.

31:31.799 --> 31:34.461
Wrap it around a tree,
three-feet thick.

31:34.601 --> 31:36.193
Drop it across a trail when
someone's hot on your ass.

31:36.303 --> 31:37.327
Remember that trick.

31:37.438 --> 31:40.271
Yeah. A det cord.
That's a nice detail.

31:40.374 --> 31:41.932
Well, you gotta get
the details right, Cliff.

31:42.042 --> 31:45.375
Otherwise, we're just making
another big craptastic movie.

31:45.479 --> 31:47.845
So, we opened this thing.
What do we find?

31:47.948 --> 31:49.245
What do we find?
What do we find?

31:49.350 --> 31:52.717
<i>Iron Man. Avengers. Dude was
a Silver Age Marvel freak.</i>

31:52.853 --> 31:55.651
And you know what he had most
of in his own personal stash?

31:55.756 --> 31:57.155
I don't know, Nick.
I wasn't there.

31:57.257 --> 31:58.383
<i>Sub-Mariner.</i>

31:58.492 --> 31:59.857
All in French What?
For some reason.

31:59.960 --> 32:01.325
Namor, prince of the deep?
Yeah.

32:01.428 --> 32:03.862
<i>Why Sub-Mariner? Isn't that,
like, one of the shit titles?</i>

32:03.964 --> 32:07.525
One theory,
tug-job material.

32:07.634 --> 32:10.125
<i>Mr. Presidente had a thing
for French-speaking fellows,</i>

32:10.270 --> 32:13.068
little Speedos and
big spears. One theory.

32:17.745 --> 32:22.341
So, you were,
like, Special Ops.

32:23.484 --> 32:25.679
What were you?
Seals? Rangers?

32:28.122 --> 32:29.589
Officially,
I'm only allowed to say

32:29.690 --> 32:31.055
that I've been
a sworn officer

32:31.158 --> 32:33.991
participating in a tactical
phase of certain missions

32:34.094 --> 32:36.221
that would make most
men want to crawl up

32:36.330 --> 32:38.992
and hide inside
their own assholes.

32:39.099 --> 32:40.691
And unofficially?

32:42.336 --> 32:44.429
I'm a goddamn American Jedi.

32:46.473 --> 32:49.067
Possible title
number one, by the way.

32:51.578 --> 32:53.910
Hey. See this?

32:58.919 --> 33:02.753
Took a frag from a Bouncing
Betty. It's an antipersonnel mine.

33:04.191 --> 33:06.751
Caved in the back
of my fucking head.

33:10.364 --> 33:11.558
Medevaced out to Germany.

33:11.665 --> 33:15.226
Got my skull rebuilt
with space-age titanium.

33:15.335 --> 33:17.462
Can't go through a metal
detector without ringing cherries,

33:17.571 --> 33:18.799
but that's cool.

33:18.906 --> 33:22.364
Lets me travel with Gilligan
just about wherever I want.

33:22.476 --> 33:23.704
Gilligan?

33:29.583 --> 33:31.141
My little buddy.

33:35.456 --> 33:37.151
That's some toothpick.

33:37.257 --> 33:42.388
Here's the kicker, though. When I
took that shrapnel, I never felt it.

33:43.363 --> 33:46.457
I mean, I felt the impact and
I felt my backside go all wet,

33:46.567 --> 33:48.125
but no real pain.

33:48.235 --> 33:50.635
Now, maybe I don't
recall events in full.

33:50.737 --> 33:54.730
They did scoop out a little gray
Spam back there, but get this.

33:55.476 --> 33:58.673
My wolf pack? They will
swear that I was ambulatory

33:58.779 --> 34:00.144
for more than 17 minutes

34:00.247 --> 34:02.807
before they forced me
to lie down. Tackled me.

34:03.650 --> 34:06.585
Even then I was looking to
monkey-fuck a Marlboro Light.

34:08.255 --> 34:11.224
There's no nerve endings
in the brain, Cliff.

34:12.391 --> 34:15.054
Remember that when
you write the scene.

34:16.396 --> 34:19.388
Yeah. There's some
really good details there.

34:20.801 --> 34:23.065
Yeah, he's really
hard to kill.

34:39.152 --> 34:41.245
Hey. Y'all make it
to the beach?

34:41.355 --> 34:43.380
Yeah, it's great.
Just keep going.

34:48.262 --> 34:50.730
Hey. You see any rangers up ahead?

34:50.831 --> 34:51.820
None that I saw.

34:51.931 --> 34:54.366
It's only, like, three
miles to the beach, we hope?

34:54.467 --> 34:57.232
Yeah, but lots of
twists and turns ahead.

34:59.907 --> 35:04.037
Hey, the further we go, the
fewer people on the trail.

35:05.178 --> 35:06.805
And your point is?

35:12.252 --> 35:14.720
Back there.
Pretend you gotta pee.

35:15.889 --> 35:17.083
Pretend?

35:22.362 --> 35:25.490
The cops in Honolulu released
a photo of the killers.

35:26.166 --> 35:29.294
Apparently, they didn't know
they were on camera.

35:31.538 --> 35:32.732
Come on.

35:34.808 --> 35:36.173
Shit.
What?

35:43.250 --> 35:45.081
It could be anybody.

35:45.185 --> 35:46.277
Are you sure about that?

35:47.721 --> 35:50.019
They don't look
familiar to you?

35:51.558 --> 35:53.549
Y'all good or what?

35:53.660 --> 35:55.218
Having a bathroom break!

35:57.464 --> 36:00.797
You are freaking me out!
It could be anybody.

36:03.403 --> 36:05.371
I mean, what do we really
know about these people

36:05.472 --> 36:07.099
aside from him
and his stories?

36:07.207 --> 36:08.674
Which, I might add,
are starting to sound

36:08.775 --> 36:10.436
more and more
bullshitty to me.

36:10.544 --> 36:11.602
Next thing we're
going to find out

36:11.712 --> 36:14.146
he's got the heart of
a baboon or something.

36:14.247 --> 36:15.737
I think he's just
trying to impress.

36:15.882 --> 36:17.975
I mean, you know, he thinks
you're going to write a movie

36:18.085 --> 36:20.053
about his life
or something.

36:20.654 --> 36:22.212
What do we know?

36:24.157 --> 36:27.354
Well, she's from Savannah. Her
father is a controlling military shit.

36:27.461 --> 36:29.429
She rebelled. She met
Nick in South Carolina,

36:29.529 --> 36:30.962
but he reminded her
too much of Daddy.

36:31.064 --> 36:32.964
He chased her until finally
giving up and moving on,

36:33.066 --> 36:35.034
but that's when she got
interested in him, of course.

36:35.135 --> 36:36.227
It's their first
time in Hawaii.

36:36.336 --> 36:38.031
They thought Waikiki
was a little Las Vegas,

36:38.138 --> 36:40.629
but they love
it here on Kauai.

36:40.741 --> 36:42.072
Girls talk.

36:45.779 --> 36:47.770
So, they were
on Oahu, too.

36:51.151 --> 36:52.778
I guess they were.

37:06.533 --> 37:09.024
Interesting guy, Cliff.

37:09.136 --> 37:10.125
Yeah.

37:10.504 --> 37:14.201
First man ever who wants to
talk while he's in the bathroom.

37:15.008 --> 37:17.101
What is going on
back there?

37:19.279 --> 37:21.804
You keep shaking that bush
so we know you're there.

37:21.915 --> 37:22.882
Keep shaking
that bush, Luke!

37:41.266 --> 37:44.360
I mean, we're supposed to be
on our honeymoon. Okay?

37:44.569 --> 37:48.164
So, slow down that
overactive brain of yours

37:48.273 --> 37:50.434
'cause I want to
enjoy myself here.

37:51.276 --> 37:53.642
Babe, we're gonna be fine.

38:07.359 --> 38:09.827
Well, I guess the beach
will still be there tomorrow.

38:09.928 --> 38:11.759
Yeah, I hope we are.

38:18.303 --> 38:25.175
All right. We got macaroni and
cheese with real imitation cheese.

38:26.077 --> 38:29.171
Honey, that's a vegetable
dish where I come from.

38:29.281 --> 38:30.646
What else you got?

38:30.815 --> 38:33.045
Vegetarian corned beef hash.

