in him, something risky,

48:35.983 --> 48:36.972
something crooked and cool.

48:39.952 --> 48:42.978
Didn't hurt that he had
his own truck, neither.

48:43.456 --> 48:44.923
He did.
Yeah.

48:45.725 --> 48:50.219
Wrong paint on one door, but damn,
he had some nice chrome wheels on it.

48:50.330 --> 48:51.729
Yeah. I know Rocky.

48:52.699 --> 48:56.999
Yeah, this one night, he
drove me out onto the lake.

48:58.805 --> 49:01.171
And it was
hot and raining.

49:01.674 --> 49:04.973
And I had the top
button of my shorts

49:05.078 --> 49:07.672
all undone for this guy, you know,

49:07.780 --> 49:11.375
and just hoping this is
why we came down here.

49:12.251 --> 49:13.513
Oh, God.

49:13.619 --> 49:18.318
You know, I remember the way
the cracks in the vinyl seat

49:18.424 --> 49:20.949
were pinching
the back of my legs.

49:21.060 --> 49:22.322
You know,
and that was bothering me,

49:22.428 --> 49:25.659
but what he was doing with
his fingers sure wasn't.

49:25.765 --> 49:29.599
And suddenly, he's in my
hand, all slippery and nice,

49:29.702 --> 49:31.533
and he's about to go off.

49:31.637 --> 49:34.970
And I'm about to come for,
like, the first time, ever.

49:37.276 --> 49:39.176
And then he puts
the headlights on.

49:42.014 --> 49:44.881
And he makes me get
out of the car to go...

49:46.251 --> 49:49.220
Go look at something
over by a pile of leaves.

49:51.790 --> 49:55.226
And it was Goldie,
the neighbor's Labrador.

49:57.295 --> 49:58.990
And he still had...

50:00.098 --> 50:02.623
